name: The Spring at Slide Mountain
description: a commonly found sign in the Catskill Mountains of New York State, specifically in areas where rivers and creeks are not plentiful and the subsequent drought presents challenges for the backpacker. The Spring is usually a bit of metal pipe stuck into the crevice between two rocks in order to elicit a fairly gentle trickle, but one sufficient enough to fill a much-needed bottle of water. In the background are the mountains within the Slide Mountain Wilderness, an area of Catskill Park full of beautiful vistas and lush sub-alpine vegetation.
